statements.sql: select `types`.*, (select count(*) from `feedbacks` where `types`.`id` = `feedbacks`.`type_id`) as `feedbacks_count`, (select count(*) from `feedbacks` where `types`.`id` = `feedbacks`.`type_id` and `polarity` = 'Positive') as `positive_count`, (select count(*) from `feedbacks` where `types`.`id` = `feedbacks`.`type_id` and `polarity` = 'Neutral') as `neutral_count`, (select count(*) from `feedbacks` where `types`.`id` = `feedbacks`.`type_id` and `polarity` = 'Negative') as `negative_count` from `types` where `model_type` = 'Feedback' order by `feedbacks_count` desc

select count(*) as feedbacks_count, count(case when polarity = 'Positive' then 1 end) as positive_count, count(case when polarity = 'Neutral' then 1 end) as neutral_count, count(case when polarity = 'Negative' then 1 end) as negative_count from `feedbacks` where `type_id` is null limit 1
